(111, 1, '2010-12-14 11:58:26', '2010-12-14 11:58:26', 'David C. Frederick works with cities, towns, counties and utilities,  providing them with accounting and financial advisory services,  including utility rate studies, cost-of-service analysis, municipal bond  issues and expert testimony at regulatory, judicial and public  hearings. He also oversees Umbaugh''s arbitrage rebate services, escrow  verifications and other attestation services.\r\n\r\nFrederick is Quality Control Partner for Umbaugh and the Chief Compliance Officer of Umbaugh Cash Advisory Services, LLC.\r\n\r\nHe is a member of the Indiana CPA  Society, the American Institute of CPAs, the Government Finance  Officers Association and other professional and utility trade  associations. He has spoken before various groups regarding accounting  and utility issues.\r\n\r\nA graduate of Ohio State  University where he also earned an MBA and a Masters of Public  Administration, Frederick joined Umbaugh in 1977 and became a partner in  1989. He is based in the Indianapolis office.', 'David C. Frederick', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'david-c-frederick', '', '', '2010-12-21 13:41:42', '2010-12-21 13:41:42', '', 0, 'http://localhost/umbaugh/?post_type=partner&p=111', 0, 'partner', '', 0),
