(326, 3, '2010-12-21 12:43:04', '2010-12-21 12:43:04', '<h2>Our Services for Local Government</h2>\r\n<strong>Financial Management</strong> - No one  who works in local government would say that financial management is  "simple."   Your constituents never think about how time consuming your  day-to-day tasks are.  Umbaugh can help you with:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Audit Preparation</li>\r\n	<li>CAFR Preparation</li>\r\n	<li>Financial Reporting</li>\r\n	<li>Tax Revenue Analysis and Management</li>\r\n	<li>Budget Preparation Assistance</li>\r\n	<li>Comprehensive Financial Planning</li>\r\n	<li>GASB 34 Compliance</li>\r\n	<li>User Fee Development</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAs you look for every <strong>cost savings and efficiency</strong>, we can also provide:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Consolidation Planning and Implementation</li>\r\n	<li>Negotiating Inter-Governmental Agreements</li>\r\n	<li>Performance Management Studies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIf you are considering a new accounting system,  let us relieve your nightmares and worry of system selection (What if it  doesn''t work?  What if we lose our data?) with:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Accounting Systems Consulting</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Capital Planning</strong> - Every unit  of government has projects that need to be done  and equipment that  needs to be upgraded or replaced.  It''s tempting to defer projects and  delay expenses, but that could catch up to you someday with a big bill   or a service failure.  We all know it''s better to plan ahead.  Umbaugh  can help you with:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Debt Management Studies</li>\r\n	<li>Project Planning and Financial Development</li>\r\n	<li>Refinancing of Existing Debt</li>\r\n	<li>Long-Range Capital Planning and Implementation</li>\r\n	<li>Developing and Evaluating Funding Alternatives</li>\r\n	<li>Financial Presentations to Elected Officials and the Public</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Bond Issuance</strong> - Bond issues are  not something you do every day, and you''ve got to get it right. The  stakes are literally too high to risk a mistake or miss an opportunity  to save. Since Umbaugh is an independent advisor, our only priority is  doing what''s best for the local governments we represent. We can  provide:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Official Statements and Bond Sale Preparations</li>\r\n	<li>Presentations to Bond Ratings Agencies</li>\r\n	<li>Evaluation of Bond Insurance Proposals</li>\r\n	<li>Competitive Bond Sales and Electronic</li>\r\n	<li>Bidding Services</li>\r\n	<li>Negotiated Bond Sales and Private Placements</li>\r\n	<li>Coordination of Bond Closings</li>\r\n	<li>Assistance to the Trustee bank</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Post Issuance</strong> - Unfortunately,  the paperwork does not go away after the bonds are sold.  You as the  bond issuer have a great deal of responsibility for reporting and  compliance, at a time when you''d much rather be paying attention to your  bond-funded project.  Umbaugh can take those worries off your plate as  well with:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>In-Progress Construction Reports</li>\r\n	<li>Arbitrage Rebate Calculations</li>\r\n	<li>Continuing Disclosure Filings</li>\r\n	<li>Post Issuance Compliance</li>\r\n	<li>Escrow Verifications</li>\r\n	<li>Parity Reports</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Local Governments', 'Operating a local governmental unit always has challenges and opportunities. You may be looking for new efficiencies, projecting changes in tax revenue, finding new revenue sources, working on long-range planning, funding buildings and improvements, or structuring the most advantageous economic development package. Our years of experience in helping others in similar situations make us uniquely qualified to help you today -- and with tomorrow''s challenges.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '206-revision-5', '', '', '2010-12-21 12:43:04', '2010-12-21 12:43:04', '', 206, 'http://dev.umbaugh.com/206-revision-5', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
